description.plain:
“It’s about romanticizing the summer, or more generally the "brighter days”. Thinking that once the weather gets better and the sun comes out, all my troubles will somehow disappear, but realizing once you arrive at that sunny moment, all you can think about is missing the feeling of the rain."

Taken from an announcement of the song’s release on Olivia’s tiktok: https://www.tiktok.com/@olivklug?lang=en&is_copy_url=1&is_from_webapp=v1

body.plain:
“It’s about romanticizing the summer, or more generally the "brighter days”. Thinking that once the weather gets better and the sun comes out, all my troubles will somehow disappear, but realizing once you arrive at that sunny moment, all you can think about is missing the feeling of the rain."

Taken from an announcement of the song’s release on Olivia’s tiktok: https://www.tiktok.com/@olivklug?lang=en&is_copy_url=1&is_from_webapp=v1

annotations: I’m already scared of the winter even though summer’s taking her sweet time to start

Klugman utilizes the idea of summer versus winter to demonstrate that she fears something that has not yet come, despite its impending inevitability. We often struggle to live in the moment, already paralyzed in fear of what we have experienced before after “having it good for so long” (possibly seasonal depression or a depressive episode).
